This paper discusses the collection and consolidation of data by third-party networks, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The focus on measuring the concentration of tracking capability suggests a potential fit with social and information networks (cs.SI) and cybercrime (cs.CY). Finally, the mention of mobile applications suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
